List images
docker images

Build image
docker build -t myapp .
docker build -t myapp:1.0 .

Remove image
docker rmi <image>
docker rmi -f <image>

Pull image
docker pull ubuntu
docker pull node:18

Push image
docker push username/myapp


4️⃣ Logs, Inspect, Exec
Container logs
docker logs <container>
docker logs -f <container>      # follow logs

Exec inside container
docker exec -it <container> /bin/bash
docker exec -it <container> sh

Inspect container
docker inspect <container>


5️⃣ Docker Compose
Start all services
docker-compose up
docker-compose up -d

Stop
docker-compose down

View logs
docker-compose logs
docker-compose logs -f

Rebuild
docker-compose up --build


6️⃣ Docker Networks
docker network ls
docker network create mynetwork
docker network inspect mynetwork
docker network connect mynetwork <container>
docker network disconnect mynetwork <container>


7️⃣ Docker Volumes
List volumes
docker volume ls

Create volume
docker volume create myvol

Inspect volume
docker volume inspect myvol

Remove volume
docker volume rm myvol


8️⃣ Save / Load Images (Your recent question 👍)
Save image to tar
docker save -o myimage.tar myapp:1.0

Load image from tar
